sentences: Scott Thomas Reeder (born May 16, 1965) is an American musician best known as the former bass player of stoner rock bands Across the River, Kyuss and The Obsessed, as well as the current bass player for Fireball Ministry.
In 1990 when Scott "Wino" Weinrich reformed The Obsessed, Reeder joined on bass and recorded two albums with the band including the landmark 1991 album Lunar Womb.
In 1990 when Scott "Wino" Weinrich reformed The Obsessed, Reeder joined on bass and recorded two albums with the band including the landmark 1991 album Lunar Womb.
Reeder left The Obsessed in 1992, and joined stoner rock band Kyuss who were without a bassist after the departure of Nick Oliveri.
Reeder remained with Kyuss until they disbanded in 1995.
In 2002, Reeder produced the British hard rock band Orange Goblin's album Coup De Grace, with former Kyuss vocalist John Garcia providing guest vocals on tracks "Made of Rats" and "Jesus Beater".
In 2003, Reeder received a call from Lars Ulrich asking him to audition for Metallica after the departure of Jason Newsted, a position eventually won by Robert Trujillo.
Reeder handled production and bass duties for BÃ¼tcher and appeared on their album Auricle in 2005.
He left the band in October 2006.
In 2006, Reeder released his first solo album TunnelVision Brilliance on which he wrote and performed all tracks by himself.
In summer 2011 he stood in at some shows of Kyuss Lives!, a band composed of former Kyuss members.
He covered a Kyuss song, "Demon Cleaner", on stage with Tool in 1998.
